Despite a resolute public policy, applied since 2005, the unemployment rate among disabled people double the average rate: 19% versus 9% for the whole population.
Discouraging ¿?
&quot;No,&quot; said Eric Blanchet, CEO of Adapt, the association which organizes the week for the employment of the disabled.
&quot;The progress made since the last fifteen years are considerable.
&quot;Back then, the unemployment rate was not twice but three times higher than average.
&quot;However, there is still much to do.&quot;
It is noteworthy that the unemployed disabled still face numerous obstacles in accessing employment.
They usually have a later age: 37% are over 50 years (17% on average).
