&quot;The 2005 law that increased contributions, has generated a lot of pressure for companies,&quot; explains Pierre Blanc.
&quot;But this improvement also reflects a true awareness, particularly among large groups.&quot;
According to the Ministry of Labor, only 59% of companies with between 20 and 49 workers with employees with disabilities in its workforce, compared with 82% of companies with between 100 and 199 workers.
